DATA CLOUD
Salesforce CRM Connector

In Data Cloud, you can establish a connection to your Salesforce CRM org. You can also use a starter data bundle to create data streams in Data Cloud. The bundle maps the data source objects to the data model objects (DMO) and establishes DMO relationships that improve your segmentation results

NOTE The Salesforce CRM Connector doesn’t support ingestion of big objects from Salesforce CRM.
Set Up a Salesforce Connection in Data Cloud
A data source and data action target are automatically created for the org where you set up Data Cloud. To connect other Salesforce orgs, you must manually set up a connection.
Enable Object and Field Permissions to Access Salesforce CRM in Data Cloud
Add the View All and Read permissions to your Data Cloud Salesforce Connector permission set in your Salesforce CRM org to ingest objects and fields into Data Cloud.
Enable Permissions to Allow Salesforce CRM Streaming
Configure the following Data Cloud permissions to allow stream processing.
Create a Salesforce CRM Data Stream
Create a data stream to begin the flow of data from a Salesforce CRM data source.
Use an Alias for a Salesforce CRM Connection
As of July ‘24, an alias is required when setting up a Salesforce CRM connection. Existing connections aren't assigned an alias. The names of the data stream and data lake object are derived from the alias.
Create a Salesforce CRM Starter Bundle
Create a data stream using a starter bundle to begin the flow of data from a Salesforce CRM source into Data Cloud.
Create a Salesforce CRM Data Stream from Financial Services Cloud (FSC) Objects
Add the permissions and license requirements in your Salesforce CRM org to ingest FSC objects.
Financial Services Cloud Bundle Data Mappings
The Financial Services Cloud data bundle for Data Cloud helps financial services firms increase employee productivity, accelerate time to value, and deepen customer trust with every interaction. These data mappings relate to Financial Services Cloud bundle available for the Salesforce CRM connector. You can add to or customize the data mappings.
Loyalty Management Bundle Data Mappings
The Loyalty Management data lets you track and manage reward and recognition programs. Loyalty Management is a Salesforce Industry Cloud application. The data is available from Salesforce Platform objects, including Loyalty Program, Loyalty Tier, and Member Benefits. These data mappings relate to the Loyalty Management bundle available in Data Cloud. You can add more mappings by the bundle, and customize the data mappings. The Loyalty Management bundle is accessible only when object permissions have been set for your Loyalty Management objects.
Omnichannel Inventory Connector
In Data Cloud, you can establish a connection to Omnichannel Inventory using the provided connector. The connection process creates the data streams and maps the data source objects to the data model objects (DMO) and establishes DMO relationships.
Salesforce Commerce Data Bundle Mappings
Salesforce Commerce standard bundles include Business-to-Business (B2B) Commerce, Direct-to-Consumer (D2C) Commerce, and Salesforce Order Management bundles. These bundles map the data source objects to the data model objects (DMO) and establish DMO relationships that enhance segmentation results.
Sales and Service Bundle Data Mappings
Use the Sales Cloud and Service Cloud datasets to manage leads, track progress, and automate sales processes. Sales Cloud data is extracted from Salesforce standard objects, such as Account, Contact, and Lead. The Service Cloud dataset lets you engage your customers at the right time as they go through the support process. These data mappings relate to the Sales Cloud and Service Cloud bundles available for the Salesforce CRM connector.
